<h1>GitHub Use Policy</h1>
<p>When you connect your GitHub account to your SWAMP account, you are asking SWAMP to rely on the security of your GitHub account.  You are responsible for protecting your GitHub account with a <a style="cursor: pointer" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="right" title="SWAMP Password Policy" data-content="Passwords must be at least 9 characters long including one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one number, and one symbol. Passwords at least 10 characters long must include one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, and one number. Symbols are encouraged. Maximum length is 200 characters ( additonal characters will be truncated. )">strong password</a>. SWAMP also recommends enabling <a target="_blank" href="https://help.github.com/articles/about-two-factor-authentication">GitHub two factor authentication</a>.</p>

<h2>Statement of Agreement</h2>
<p>If you accept this responsibility, click "I accept" then click "Sign Up!" to create and link a new SWAMP acccount with GitHub, or "Link Existing" if you already have a SWAMP account and you'd like to link it to your GitHub account. If you have questions, please contact the Help Desk at <code><a href="mailto:support@continuousassurance.org">support@continuousassurance.org</a></code>.</p>

